Document: AudioStreamGenerator
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamgenerator.rst
Summary: An AudioStream that generates audio data via a script, commonly used for procedural audio generation.
AudioStreamGenerator is a type of audio stream that does not play back sounds on its own; instead, it expects a script to generate audio data for it. See also AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.

Here's a sample on how to use it to generate a sine wave:

GDScript:
    var playback # Will hold the AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.
    @onready var sample_hz = $AudioStreamPlayer.stream.mix_rate
    var pulse_hz = 440.0 # The frequency of the sound wave.
    var phase = 0.0

    func _ready():
        $AudioStreamPlayer.play()
        playback = $AudioStreamPlayer.get_stream_playback()
        fill_buffer()

    func fill_buffer():
        var increment = pulse_hz / sample_hz
        var frames_available = playback.get_frames_available()

        for i in range(frames_available):
            playback.push_frame(Vector2.ONE * sin(phase * TAU))
            phase = fmod(phase + increment, 1.0)

C#:
    [Export] public AudioStreamPlayer Player { get; set; }

    private AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback _playback; // Will hold the AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback.
    private float _sampleHz;
    private float _pulseHz = 440.0f; // The frequency of the sound wave.
    private double phase = 0.0;

    public override void _Ready()
    {
        if (Player.Stream is AudioStreamGenerator generator) // Type as a generator to access MixRate.
        {
            _sampleHz = generator.MixRate;
            Player.Play();
            _playback = (AudioStreamGeneratorPlayback)Player.GetStreamPlayback();
            FillBuffer();
        }
    }

    public void FillBuffer()
    {
        float increment = _pulseHz / _sampleHz;
        int framesAvailable = _playback.GetFramesAvailable();

        for (int i = 0; i < framesAvailable; i++)
        {
            _playback.PushFrame(Vector2.One * (float)Mathf.Sin(phase * Mathf.Tau));
            phase = Mathf.PosMod(phase + increment, 1.0);
        }
    }

In the example above, the "AudioStreamPlayer" node must use an AudioStreamGenerator as its stream. The fill_buffer function provides audio data for approximating a sine wave.

See also AudioEffectSpectrumAnalyzer for performing real-time audio spectrum analysis.

Note: Due to performance constraints, this class is best used from C# or from a compiled language via GDExtension. If you still want to use this class from GDScript, consider using a lower mix_rate such as 11,025 Hz or 22,050 Hz.
---CHUNK---
Document: AudioStreamGenerator
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamgenerator.rst
Summary: This document provides an overview of the AudioStreamGenerator class in Godot Engine.

Inherits: AudioStream < Resource < RefCounted < Object

AudioStreamGenerator
AudioStreamGenerator is a special type of AudioStream that can be used to generate audio procedurally.

It works by providing a callback function that is called whenever new audio data is needed. This callback function is responsible for generating the audio samples and returning them to the AudioStreamPlayer.

This is useful for generating dynamic audio effects, procedural music, or any other type of audio that needs to be generated on the fly.

Methods
- void push_buffer(buffer: PackedByteArray)
Pushes a buffer of audio data to the generator. The buffer must be in the format expected by the AudioStreamGenerator.

- void push_frame(frame: Vector2)
Pushes a single audio frame (left and right channels) to the generator.

- int get_buffer_size()
Returns the current size of the audio buffer in samples.

- int get_latency()
Returns the current latency of the audio generator in seconds.

Properties
- int mix_rate
The mix rate of the audio generator in Hz. This should match the project's audio output mix rate.

- int channels
The number of audio channels. Currently only mono (1) and stereo (2) are supported.

Example
Here's a simple example of how to use AudioStreamGenerator to generate a sine wave:

GDScript:
```gdscript
extends Node

var audio_stream_generator = AudioStreamGenerator.new()
var audio_stream_player = AudioStreamPlayer.new()
var frequency = 440.0
var sample_rate = ProjectSettings.get_setting("audio/general/mix_rate")
var time = 0.0
var amplitude = 0.5

func _ready():
    add_child(audio_stream_player)
    audio_stream_player.stream = audio_stream_generator
    audio_stream_player.play()

func _process(delta):
    var buffer_size = int(sample_rate * delta)
    var buffer = PackedByteArray()
    for i in range(buffer_size):
        var sample = sin(time * frequency * 2.0 * PI) * amplitude
        buffer.append(int(sample * 32767.0)) # Convert to 16-bit integer
        time += 1.0 / sample_rate
    audio_stream_generator.push_buffer(buffer)
```

C#:
```csharp
using Godot;
using System;

public class AudioGeneratorExample : Node
{
    private AudioStreamGenerator _audioStreamGenerator = new AudioStreamGenerator();
    private AudioStreamPlayer _audioStreamPlayer = new AudioStreamPlayer();
    private float _frequency = 440.0f;
    private int _sampleRate = ProjectSettings.GetSetting("audio/general/mix_rate").AsInt32();
    private float _time = 0.0f;
    private float _amplitude = 0.5f;

    public override void _Ready()
    {
        AddChild(_audioStreamPlayer);
        _audioStreamPlayer.Stream = _audioStreamGenerator;
        _audioStreamPlayer.Play();
    }

    public override void _Process(float delta)
    {
        int bufferSize = (int)(_sampleRate * delta);
        PackedByteArray buffer = new PackedByteArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < bufferSize; i++)
        {
            float sample = (float)Math.Sin(_time * _frequency * 2.0 * Math.PI) * _amplitude;
            buffer.Add((int)(sample * 32767.0f)); // Convert to 16-bit integer
            _time += 1.0f / _sampleRate;
        }
        _audioStreamGenerator.PushBuffer(buffer);
    }
}
```
